detectors.description:
Reentrancy in MiniMeToken.approve(address,uint256) ():
	External calls:
	- ! TokenController(controller).onApprove(msg.sender,_spender,_amount) ()
	State variables written after the call(s):
	- allowed[msg.sender][_spender] = _amount ()
	MiniMeToken.allowed () can be used in cross function reentrancies:
	- MiniMeToken.allowance(address,address) ()
	- MiniMeToken.approve(address,uint256) ()
	- MiniMeToken.approveAndCall(address,uint256,bytes) ()
	- MiniMeToken.transferFrom(address,address,uint256) ()
detectors.markdown:
Reentrancy in [MiniMeToken.approve(address,uint256)]():
	External calls:
	- [! TokenController(controller).onApprove(msg.sender,_spender,_amount)]()
	State variables written after the call(s):
	- [allowed[msg.sender][_spender] = _amount]()
	[MiniMeToken.allowed]() can be used in cross function reentrancies:
	- [MiniMeToken.allowance(address,address)]()
	- [MiniMeToken.approve(address,uint256)]()
	- [MiniMeToken.approveAndCall(address,uint256,bytes)]()
	- [MiniMeToken.transferFrom(address,address,uint256)]()

detectors.description:
Controlled.changeController(address) () should emit an event for: 
	- controller = _newController ()

Owned.changeOwner(address) () should emit an event for: 
	- owner = _newOwner ()

Owned.changeOwner(address)._newOwner () lacks a zero-check on :
		- owner = _newOwner ()

detectors.description:
Reentrancy in MiniMeToken.doTransfer(address,address,uint256) ():

	- previousBalanceFrom = balanceOfAt(_from,block.number) ()
		- parentToken.balanceOfAt(_owner,parentSnapShotBlock) ()
	- ! TokenController(controller).onTransfer(_from,_to,_amount) ()
	- previousBalanceTo = balanceOfAt(_to,block.number) ()
		- parentToken.balanceOfAt(_owner,parentSnapShotBlock) ()
	Event emitted after the call(s):
	- Transfer(_from,_to,_amount) ()

	- [! TokenController(controller).onTransfer(_from,_to,_amount)]()
	- [previousBalanceTo = balanceOfAt(_to,block.number)]()
		- [parentToken.balanceOfAt(_owner,parentSnapShotBlock)]()
	Event emitted after the call(s):
